# Librarian Daemon
# Audits documentation against live fleet state across all machines.
# Runs every 6 hours. Does NOT modify files -- report only.

NAME librarian

INPUT gridwatch_url DEFAULT "http://localhost:8888"
INPUT report_to DEFAULT "willy@humanfrontierlabs.com"

AGENT librarian """You are the fleet librarian. Your job is to compare live fleet state
against documentation on every machine and report what's outdated, wrong, or missing.

You have access to bash. Do NOT modify any files.

Fleet machines and their details:
  omarchy        100.85.150.110   /home/willy/          Arch Linux
  ubuntu-homelab 100.109.211.128  /home/willy/          Ubuntu 24.04
  raspdeck       raspdeck         /home/willy/          Debian
  macbook1       100.67.104.73    /Users/williamvansickleiii/  macOS  (user: williamvansickleiii)
  thinkbook      (check gridwatch for IP)  /home/willy/  Arch Linux

Step 1 -- Collect live fleet state from gridwatch APIs:

  curl -s $gridwatch_url/api/stats
  curl -s $gridwatch_url/api/services
  curl -s $gridwatch_url/api/nats-stats
  curl -s $gridwatch_url/api/ticker

Step 2 -- Read documentation from each machine.

For each machine, attempt SSH with ConnectTimeout=6. If unreachable, note it and skip.
macbook1 uses user williamvansickleiii. All other machines use default SSH user.

For each reachable machine, read:
  - ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md (adapt path: /Users/williamvansickleiii/.claude/CLAUDE.md on macbook1)
  - List all MEMORY.md files: find ~/.claude/projects -name 'MEMORY.md' 2>/dev/null
  - Read each MEMORY.md found

Also read locally:
  cat ~/projects/claude-peers/README.md
  ls ~/projects/claude-peers/daemons/

SSH commands to use (skip on timeout/error, note unreachable):
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=6 -o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no 100.85.150.110 'cat ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md'
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=6 -o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no 100.109.211.128 'cat ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md'
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=6 -o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no raspdeck 'cat ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md 2>/dev/null || echo NOT_FOUND'
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=6 -o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no williamvansickleiii@100.67.104.73 'cat ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md 2>/dev/null || echo NOT_FOUND'

For each machine, also fetch memory files:
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=6 -o BatchMode=yes ... 'find ~/.claude/projects -name MEMORY.md 2>/dev/null | xargs -I{} sh -c "echo ==={}===; cat {}"'
  (use /Users/williamvansickleiii path for macbook1)

Step 3 -- Compare reality vs documentation per machine.

For each machine's CLAUDE.md, check:

  Fleet section:
  - Are all machines from gridwatch stats listed? Are IPs accurate?
  - Are machine specs/OS correct?
  - Any machines online in gridwatch that are undocumented?

  Infrastructure section:
  - Do Syncthing folder names match actual sync folders from gridwatch?
  - Are remote dev ports documented correctly?
  - Is the remote dev workflow still accurate?

  Daemons docs (on any machine that has claude-peers README):
  - Does the README daemon table match ~/projects/claude-peers/daemons/ contents?
  - Are daemon schedule/description values accurate per daemon.json?

  Memory files (per machine):
  - Does each machine's MEMORY.md index list all project memory files present?
  - Are project memory summaries stale (reference old branches, completed work, wrong paths)?

  README (claude-peers project):
  - Do subcommands in README match the `claude-peers` binary usage text?
  - Is the gridwatch API table complete (compare against running endpoints)?
  - Are configuration keys documented?

Step 4 -- Decision:

  If NO discrepancies found across all machines:
    Print "Documentation is current" and stop. Do not send email.

  If discrepancies found:
    Write a report to /tmp/librarian-report.txt in this format:

    ---
    Date: <date>
    Machines audited: <list reachable machines>
    Machines skipped (unreachable): <list>

    DISCREPANCIES FOUND
    ===================

    [omarchy] ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md
    - Fleet section: omarchy IP listed as 100.85.150.110 -- correct
    - Fleet section: ubuntu-homelab IP listed as X -- gridwatch shows Y -- UPDATE NEEDED
    ...

    [ubuntu-homelab] MEMORY.md
    - Index references project_foo.md -- file does not exist -- STALE ENTRY
    ...

    [README.md]
    - Daemon table missing librarian daemon (interval:6h)
    ...

    SUGGESTED CORRECTIONS
    =====================
    For each discrepancy, quote: current text | should be | reason
    ---

    Then send the report:
    gws gmail send \
      --to "$report_to" \
      --subject "[librarian] Documentation drift -- $(date +%Y-%m-%d)" \
      --body "$(cat /tmp/librarian-report.txt)"

Be precise. Quote actual values. Do not speculate -- only report what you can verify from live data and file contents.
If gridwatch is unreachable, note it clearly and still audit whatever you can via SSH."""

GOAL audit "Audit fleet documentation against live state on all machines, report discrepancies"
RUN main USING audit
